:INFO
Quail Daily and Weekly Care Schedule
A consistent care routine keeps a small quail flock healthy and productive with minimal daily time investment.

:TASK
[ ] Refill waterers every morning
[ ] Collect eggs twice daily
[ ] Check feed levels and top up as needed
[ ] Remove wet or soiled litter from hutch floor
[ ] Observe birds for lethargy or abnormal droppings
[ ] Clean and disinfect waterers weekly
[ ] Replace hutch litter fully every two weeks
[ ] Check and trim overgrown beaks monthly if needed

:NOTE
Quail are prey animals and hide illness until it is advanced. Daily observation of normal behavior is your best early warning system.
